    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="original">
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP004_01.jpg" n="1"/>
                <p>Dne <date when="1944-10-20">20.10.1944</date> byl v <placeName ref="#l0" type="ehri">Osvětímě</placeName> v lágru E sestaven <term
                        ref="#t556" type="subject">pracovní</term>
                    <term ref="#t518" type="subject">transport</term>. Při kontrolní prohlídce byli pro tělesnou slabost vyšetřujícím <term
                        ref="#t287" type="subject">lékařem</term>
                    <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term> vyňati: <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri">Zeev Scheck</persName>,
                        <persName ref="#https://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/91551-egon-haas" type="ehri">Egon Haas</persName> a <persName
                        ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold" type="ehri">Bertl Simonsohn</persName>, protože vypadali velmi hubeně. Byli utišováni, že
                    budou posláni jako <q><foreign xml:lang="de"><distinct type="camp_language">Stubendienst</distinct></foreign></q> na nějaký čas do
                        <term ref="#t496" type="subject">lágru</term>, aby se zotavili a pak že budou posláni na <term ref="#t556" type="subject"
                        >práci</term>. Přes to tušili, oč jde a hlavně <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri">Zeev</persName> snažil se dostat
                        <term ref="#t518" type="subject">transportu</term> tím, že ukazoval svaly a ujišťoval, že je na těžkou práci zvyklý, že jenom
                    tak hubeně vypadá a že je úplně zdráv. <persName ref="#https://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/91551-egon-haas" type="ehri"
                        >Egon Haas</persName> a <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold" type="ehri">Bertl Simonsohn</persName> se k tomu přidali.
                    Přes to nepochodili a jenom proto, že scházeli lidé do <term ref="#t518" type="subject">transportu</term>, byli na konec k <term
                        ref="#t518" type="subject">transportu</term> připojení.</p>
                <p>Je zajímavé, že z tohoto <term ref="#t518" type="subject">transportu</term> zůstali celkem 4 lidé na živu, mezi nimi <persName
                        ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri">Zeev</persName> a <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold" type="ehri"
                        >Bertl</persName>.</p>
                <p>Protokol přijala: Vlastnoruční podpis svědka:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_kratkova_marta" type="ehri">Marta Kratková</persName>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_nasch_erich" type="ehri">Dr. Nasch</persName>
                </p>
                <p>Za <term ref="#t657" type="subject">dokumentační akci</term>:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri">Zeev Scheck</persName>
                </p>
                <p>Za archiv:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_schmiedt_alexander" type="ehri">Alex. Schmiedt</persName>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="transcription">
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP004_01.jpg" n="1"/>
                <p>On <date when="1944-10-20">20.10.1944</date> a <term ref="#t556" type="subject">labor</term><term ref="#t518" type="subject"
                        >transport</term> was put together in <placeName ref="#l0" type="ehri">Auschwitz</placeName> in camp E. During the medical
                    check-up, the examining <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term>
                    <term ref="#t287" type="subject">doctor</term>removed the following people due to physical weakness: <persName
                        ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri">Zeev Scheck</persName>, <persName ref="#egon-haas" type="ehri">Egon Haas</persName>, and
                        <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold" type="ehri">Bertl Simonsohn</persName>, because they looked very thin. They were
                    assured that they would be sent as <q><foreign xml:lang="de"><distinct type="camp_language">Stubendienst</distinct></foreign></q>
                    to the <term ref="#t496" type="subject">camp</term> for a short time so that they could get better and then be sent to <term
                        ref="#t556" type="subject">work</term>. But they knew what was going on and <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri"
                        >Zeev</persName> especially tried to get onto the <term ref="#t518" type="subject">transport</term> by showing his muscles and
                    vowing that he was used to hard work, that he only appeared thin, but that he was completely healthy. <persName ref="#egon-haas"
                        type="ehri">Egon Haas</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold" type="ehri">Bertl Simonsohn</persName> joined
                    him. They weren’t successful, but were added to the <term ref="#t518" type="subject">transport</term> in the end only because some
                    people were missing.</p>
                <p>It’s interesting that only 4 people survived this <term ref="#t518" type="subject">transport</term>, and <persName
                        ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri">Zeev</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold" type="ehri"
                        >Bertl</persName> are among them.</p>
                <p>Statement was accepted by: <space> </space>Signature of the witness:</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_kratkova_marta" type="ehri">Marta Kratková</persName>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_nasch_erich" type="ehri">Dr.Nasch</persName></p>
                <p>On behalf of the <term ref="#t657" type="subject">documentary campaign</term>:</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri">Zeev Scheck</persName></p>
                <p>On behalf of the archive:</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_schmiedt_alexander" type="ehri">Alex. Schmiedt</persName></p>
            </div>
